properties.sfomuseum:description: Handwritten letter from Harold M. Bixby to his wife, Debby Bixby, dated August 23, 1933, on stationery from the Manila Hotel; includes description of Manila, planned flights to Iloilo and Zamboanga, brief discussion of negotiations for routes in Manila; mentions Mr. [Norman] Hill and Governor General [Frank] Murphy.
